cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel approach to training generative adversarial networks (GANs) using a consistency term and connects it with semi-supervised learning. It also discusses the challenges in training GANs and proposes an alternative direction to avoid the caveats in the minmax two-player training of GANs. The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it evaluates the proposed approach on the CIFAR-10 dataset and discusses the photo-realistic samples generated by the model. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a new approach to training GANs and discusses the state-of-the-art results achieved on the CIFAR-10 dataset. The paper also involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it discusses the training procedure of GANs and the Lipschitz continuity of the discriminator. Finally, the paper involves graphics (cs.GR) as it discusses the generation of photo-realistic samples by the proposed approach.
